{
  "texts": [
    "Here, start j ∈ [1, n] and end j ∈ [1, n] denote the starting and ending indices of the jth entity, respectively, where start j ≤ end j and t j ∈ {rare disease, disease, symptom, sign} is the entity type.",
    "We letx start j: x end j = [x start j x start j+1 • • • x end j-1 x end j]denote the textual span from x start j to x end j and let Ŷ:= { ŷ1, ŷ2,..., ŷ m } denote the model-predicted label vector whereŷk = {x ŝtart k: x ênd k, tk }, 0 ≤ k ≤ m ≤ nis the tuple for the kth predicted entity.",
    "Figure 1 shows an example where an NER model recognizes one of two named entities from the input, \"Keratomalacia is a cause of corneal scarring.\"",
    "Here, the model correctly identified the rare disease, \"keratomalacia,\" but missed \"corneal scarring\" as a sign.",
    "DatasetTo study the NER performance of LLMs for rare diseases, we used the RareDis corpus, which consists of n = 832 texts containing descriptions of rare diseases from the National Organization for Rare Disorders database [19]."
